A BUGATTI Chiron and a Porsche 911 were involved in a very expensive crash. The incident happened in Switzerland and caused a damage worth more than £3 million (about R62 million). Four cars were damaged in the crash, with one driver sustaining serious injuries. It’s reported that the Bugatti and the Porsche 911 attempted an overtake at the same time, and they crashed into a motor home and another car, a Mercedes-Benz C-Class wagon. The driver of the Mercedes suffered serious injuries and was taken to hospital by the emergency services.  